President Obama has nominated Joseph H. Gale for a second term as a Judge to the United States Tax Court. Gale is currently a Judge on the Tax Court and has a background in tax law, having served as the Minority Staff Director and Chief Counsel of the U.S. Senate Committee on Finance and as the Committee's Chief Tax Counsel. He has also worked as an attorney in private practice. Gale received his A.B. from Princeton University and his J.D. from the University of Virginia School of Law. President Obama praised Gale for his integrity and commitment to public service.